Senator representing Plateau South Senatorial District, Senator Ignatius Longjan is dead. Reports said Longjan, who was also a former Deputy Governor of Plateau State, allegedly died in a Turkish hospital. Senator Longjan, aged 75, died on Sunday evening in Abuja after falling ill for several weeks. Confirming the report, former Chief of Staff, Chief John Dafa’an, said: “It is true, our father and distinguished Senator representing Plateau South is death, baba died after battling with illness for a long time in Turkey,” he said. Gov. Bello commiserates with victims of bandits attack He was a member of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) and was the Vice-Chairman, Senate Committee on Culture and Tourism until his death. Detail Shortly…